I have been shopping here for a few months and have been increasingly confused by how rude the staff can be while others are polite. Today a cashier said absolutely nothing to me during the entire transaction, even when I said "thank you" he just glared at me. He didn't even card me for the beer I was buying. I have had nearly identical experiences with at least two other cashiers. Most of the cashiers are too lazy to deal with the bag tax, even when I tell them that I will need to pay for bags. Then I got home and found that the loaf of bread I bought is covered with mold. It's too bad that some of the staff have to put up with these employees because I have had great experiences at the meat and cheese counter, they have handled the pandemic well and the store is generally clean and sells clean food. It is a nice place until you get to the check-out area or get home to open your bags and find mold. After this I will be looking for a new grocery store.  The community deserves better.
